body:
@ijuma Perhaps you can take a gander at this one. The bulk of the changes are just the renaming we discussed in the thread. I went with a slightly different name because the directory for the code and the name in the ducktape code are semi- tied together. `DEV_BRANCH` seemed a reasonable compromise.

Buried in the changes are the few test additions. I'm actually not that familiar with those tests and they include parameters that I was a bit unclear on why we have the set of parameterizations we have, so look carefully at those changes.

I kicked off a test for the core system tests and it looks mostly ok here: https://jenkins.confluent.io/job/system-test-kafka-branch-builder/691/consoleFull There are some failures, but some are known (the issue with ProduceConsumeValidate). The others I'm hoping someone can explain -- I'm not sure why a cluster ID in ZK (or lack thereof) would suddenly show up in these tests.

What about `GlobalKTable` -- I believe, it did not exists when the Jira was created.
\cc @dguy 
@guozhangwang I would love to get this into `0.10.2` -- I guess we could have a follow up PR for `GlobalKTable`, too, if you just want to merge it as is.
